<Module>
	<ModulePrefs title="Organic Poetry Gadget" height="320">
		<Require feature="wave" /> 
		<Require feature="dynamic-height" />
	</ModulePrefs>
	<Content type="html">
		<![CDATA[
		<link type="text/css" rel="stylesheet"
					href="http://organic-poetry.googlecode.com/hg/poetry.css"
					/>
		<link type="text/css" rel="stylesheet"
					href="http://organic-poetry.googlecode.com/hg/jquery-ui-1.7.2.custom.css"
					/>
		<script type="text/javascript"
						src="http://organic-poetry.googlecode.com/hg/json2min.js"></script>
		<script type="text/javascript"
						src="http://organic-poetry.googlecode.com/hg/jquery-1.3.2.min.js"></script>
		<script type="text/javascript"
						src="http://organic-poetry.googlecode.com/hg/jquery-ui-1.7.2.custom-drag-resize.min.js"></script>
		<script type="text/javascript"
						src="http://organic-poetry.googlecode.com/hg/organic.js"></script>
		<div id="op-container">
			<div id="user-guide-link"></div>
			<div id="user-guide" class="hidden">
				<ol>
					<li>If you have newly inserted the gadget into a wave, all you will see is the "Start" node. If it's not Blue, click on it. If it's blue already, it's the current node/word.</li>
					<li>Type a phrase or sentence into the little text box, and press Add.</li>
					<li>Your sentence gets broken up into words, and a branch is created vertically below the current node.</li>
					<li>Select any word that you want to create another branch on.</li>
					<li>Preferably move it to a spot that has some empty space below it.</li>
					<li>Type in some more words to continue from the selected word, and press Add.</li>
					<li>Move words around for readability.</li>
					<li>Select another word and Repeat.</li>
				</ol>
			</div>
			<div id="debug">Waiting for dragging the image get started...</div>
			<div id="controls">
				<input id="newWord" type="text" value=""/>
				<input id="add" type="button" value="Add"/>
				Or
				<input id="delete" type="button" value="Delete Subtree"/>
			</div>
			<div id="organic-poetry">
				<canvas id="op-back" width="295px" height="295px"></canvas>
			</div>
		</div>
		]]>
	</Content>
</Module>